title: WEDNESDAY - QB change in Philly 2020
itunes:title: WEDNESDAY - QB change in Philly 2020
description:
Lamar Jackson was back for the Ravens (0:07) as he led Baltimore to the win over the Cowboys. We'll hear from head coach John Harbaugh about the win (0:50). Unfortunately, we didn't get to see Dez Bryant (0:33) take on his former team as he was a late scratch due to a positive COVID-19 test. In Philadelphia, the Eagles make a change at quarterback (1:57) as Jalen Hurts takes over from Carson Wentz. Head coach Doug Pederson (2:28) says the move was made to spark the offense. The Cardinals get a key part of their offense back (3:19), and we'll preview the rematch of Super Bowl LIII as the Patriots take on the Rams (3:33) on Thursday Night Football
